1.auto-startup: gnome-session-properties
vlogin
gnome-panel
xmodmap /home/user/.Xmodmap

2.add to local /etc/crontab:
*/30 *    * * *   user    /bin/tmsync
*/10 *    * * *   user    /home/user/.bin/local/check-new-mail

3.add to local /etc/sudoers:    sudo visudo
sudo chgrp root vsudoer
sudo chown root vsudoer
chmod 440 vsudoer
ln -s /home/user/.bin/local/vsudoer /etc/sudoers.d/

4.add samba
edit /etc/samba/smb.conf to add the smb-dir.
use smbpasswd  -a xxx to add your user's name.
service smb restart
maybe unused:
service  iptables stop
setenforce 0
vi /etc/selinux/config
change 'SELINUX=enforcing' to 'SELINUX=disabled'

